<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="159" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1241,2034]" pageId="7" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1380,1406]" pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[430,516,1380,1407]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Length of head (
<figureCitation box="[727,810,1380,1406]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) subequal (1.03) to width in dorsal view; basal half of clypeus with middle carina; lower half of frons with moderate punctures and upper half mostly impunctate; vertex (
<figureCitation box="[160,241,1449,1475]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) with a few sparse punctures; OOD 1.48× POD and 0.42× OCD (
<figureCitation box="[975,1059,1449,1475]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1284,1449,1475]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) with weakly anterior carina and medially lacking, anterior half of dorsum densely punctate and posterior half sparsely punctate; lateral side of pronotum ventrally densely striate; near lateral and posterior margin of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1369,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) with dense punctures, medially with a comparatively narrow longitudinal groove and base of groove almost as wide as apex, surrounding area of the groove largely impunctate, dorsum without bordering carina between horizontal and posterior surfaces; ventral margin of hind femur medially with obtuse and short prominence; T1 (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1328,1623,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) with anteriorly transverse carina, behind the carina with a row of dense punctures; T6 (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1129,1657,1684]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) with sparse punctures and apically impunctate and coriaceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1241,2034]" pageId="7" pageNumber="159">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[273,359,1727,1754]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Medio-apical margin of clypeus triangularly emarginated; clypeus with a strongly middle carina; frons wholly with dense punctures; vertex with sparser and smaller punctures than those on frons; pronotal transverse carina strongly present; anteriorly two-thirds of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[964,1049,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) transversely strongly striate and even carinate, and posterior one-third with a few sparse punctures; dorsum of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1264,1831,1857]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with medially irregularly reticulate carinae forming an closed area; lateral surface of propodeum anteriorly with striae extending metapleuron, rest of the surface strongly and coarsely reticulo-punctate; T1 (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1125,1900,1926]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) anteriorly with transverse carina; S1 medially strongly carinate; dorsal surface of hind coxa longitudinally, acutely carinated; T7 with sparse punctures, length of S7 0.4× length of the T7 (
<figureCitation box="[670,751,1971,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="159">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) in lateral view.
</paragraph>
